    <item>
      <title>Re: Class Issues List - Update</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=druidbalance&amp;message.id=6127#M6127</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;1. Healing Toolkit. &lt;FONT color=#0066ff&gt;(EXPANDED)&lt;BR&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;BR&gt;In light of recent statements about no changes being made to 10-second heals, and the limited changes being made to direct heals, the overall limited nature of the druid healing "toolkit" is obvious. Right now, it essentially is limited to two lines: the big 10-second heals, and the moderately fast direct heals. As the first becomes more obsolete&amp;nbsp;(apparently by design), that leaves druids with only one healing spell line.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;If SOE intends druids to be able to function in the healing role going forward, then one or two additional tools need to be added to the kit to enable druids to do so. This is so even with Stances, as it appears that a healing stance will only affect the magnitude of the tools given, and not expand the number of tools available.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Possibilities for additional tools include:&lt;BR&gt;- faster heals (nb. this could be accomplished by a new faster-casting heal spell line, lowering the cast time of the existing fast line, by a Quick Healing AA, by a spell haste spell, or some alternative means)&lt;BR&gt;- group heal&lt;BR&gt;- HoT&lt;BR&gt;- group HoT (consider reducting reuse time of SotW line, possibly with new AA)&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;- a form of Divine Arbitration&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;In addition, while the 10-second heals remain in the game, there is no good reason for certain limitations to remain on TR and KR, if druids are expected to be able to act as main healers.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; The following changes are requested (see &lt;A href="http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=druidbalance&amp;amp;message.id=6015" target=_blank&gt;&lt;FONT color=#fac400&gt;http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=druidbalance&amp;amp;message.id=6015&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/A&gt;&amp;nbsp;for&amp;nbsp;some cleric comments and suggestions on this)&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;-reduce casting cost&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;-remove percentage cap&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;-allow healing gift to impact (i.e., crit)&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;2. Stances&amp;nbsp; &lt;FONT color=#0066ff&gt;(NEW)&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;It has been nearly half a year since there has been any additional word on stances.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; While druids appreciate the desire to see spell changes in place first, the length of time and lack of formal communication from the Dev Team has lead many druids to give up on stances (and the game itself, in some cases).&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; The initial excitement&amp;nbsp;generated by the initial disclosure regarding stances has long since dissipated.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Some formal communication (i.e., a post by a&amp;nbsp;Dev Team member)&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;regarding current thought on stances, timelines, etc., is requested.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; Needless to say, druids also want stances added to the game as soon as possible, as the conditions causing the need for stances still continue, adversely impacting druid gameplay right now.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;3.&amp;nbsp;Percentage Debuffs &lt;FONT color=#0066ff&gt;(NEW)&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Druid debuffs are fixed, and thus do not scale up with increases in mob effectiveness and power.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; One or more of the debuff spells should be looked at for a switch to a percentage-based debuff to attack and armor class.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;4.&amp;nbsp; Glacier Breath and Eci: &lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;(currently being evaluated)&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;a.&amp;nbsp; Glacier Breath effectively does NOTHING additional compared to Eci.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; It is a "wasted" spell.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Glacier Breath:&amp;nbsp; current&amp;nbsp; resist check 0, 312 mana, decrease CR by 55, decrease AC by 29&lt;BR&gt;Eci : resist check 0, 250 mana, decrease CR by 55, decrease AC by 25&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;In other words, 62 more mana gets only a negligible -4 decrease in AC.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; At the least, there should be a negative resistance adjustment (e.g., -50).&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;b.&amp;nbsp; Glacier Breath and Eci both need a resist adjustment comparable to Hand of Ro line.&lt;BR&gt;This can be seen by comparing other debuffs.&amp;nbsp; Of 14 resist debuffs:&lt;BR&gt;3 are unresistable&lt;BR&gt;3 have a -200 resist adjust (all take off 55 points or more)&lt;BR&gt;5 have a -50 resist adjust&lt;BR&gt;3 have no resist adjust (Malosinia, Bard ancient debuff, Eci/Glacier)&lt;/P&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;5. Charm issues &lt;FONT color=#0066ff&gt;(REVISED)&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;- need mobs at higher levels and in expansions to charm;&amp;nbsp; expansion zones need to include DC'able mobs&lt;BR&gt;- tag mobs that should be animals as animals&amp;nbsp; (suggested list of mobs by zone being prepared)&lt;/P&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;6.&amp;nbsp; Group/updated cures &lt;FONT color=#0066ff&gt;(NEW)&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;- Pure Blood has become severely underpowered in light of current content, and an upgrade to the single target cure spell is needed&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;- a group cure spell also is needed, in light of current content&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;- alternatively, further reduction in the radiant cure reuse time would address many of the group cure issues&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;7. Move Call of the Wild to lower level&amp;nbsp; &lt;FONT color=#0066ff&gt;(NEW)&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;-the need for a summon-to-corpse spell exists for druids other than level 70 druids&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;8. More shape changing forms and ideally special abilities for each &lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;(currently being evaluated)&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;9. Wolf form problems&amp;nbsp;&lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt; (currently being evaluated)&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;10. Improved run speed&amp;nbsp; &lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;(currently being evaluated)&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;- "Spirit of Horse":&amp;nbsp; faster SoW closer to run speed of higher end horse or&amp;nbsp; base Selo's,&amp;nbsp; with or without lev effects (floating effect of FoE causes motion sickness, excessive lag for many players)&lt;BR&gt;- faster SoW;&amp;nbsp; indoor SoW&lt;BR&gt;- revised Spirit of Cheetah spell (druid only, longer duration, no long recast time)&lt;/P&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
      <pubDate>Sat, 06 Aug 2005 01:07:17 GMT</pubDate>
